{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771518568,"nonce":"NhP7dKuPKL8TFra1xnwkTZlc8ks=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87sQ8Kg","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/234","origin":"github"},"title":"Incremental package quality improvement process","message":"## Problem\n\nWe have many ROS 2 packages across the workspace, and their quality varies — some lack tests, CI, pre-commit hooks, or documentation. Tackling all packages at once is overwhelming and impractical.\n\n## Proposal: Incremental Quality Improvement\n\nAdopt an **\"improve as you go\"** model: whenever an agent works on a package it hasn't touched recently, it also brings that package closer to a defined quality standard. This happens naturally alongside feature work rather than as a separate large-scale effort.\n\n### Suggested Mechanisms\n\n#### 1. Package Quality Checklist (`.agent/knowledge/package_quality_standards.md`)\n\nA knowledge file defining the gold standard for ROS 2 packages in this workspace. Agents consult it when entering a package. Categories include:\n\n- **Testing**: ament_lint_auto integration, unit tests (gtest/pytest), launch tests for nodes, pluginlib load tests for plugins, explicit `-DBUILD_TESTING=ON` in CI\n- **CI**: GitHub Actions workflow on the default branch, pre-commit hooks configured, all hooks passing\n- **Documentation**: Package README with description/topics/parameters/services, `.agents/README.md` with architecture overview, accurate `package.xml` metadata\n- **Code quality**: Modern CMake targets (not `ament_target_dependencies`), copyright headers, consistent formatting (or documented exceptions)\n- **Infrastructure**: `.pre-commit-config.yaml`, CI badge in README\n\n#### 2. CLAUDE.md \"Audit on Entry\" Rule\n\nAdd a rule to CLAUDE.md requiring agents to run a quick quality check when entering a package for the first time in a session. The audit identifies gaps vs. the standard and the agent files a single tracking issue for improvements (if one doesn't already exist), then proceeds with the primary task.\n\n#### 3. Audit Script (`.agent/scripts/audit_package.sh`)\n\nA lightweight script that checks a package directory for quality indicators:\n- `[ ] CI workflow exists`\n- `[ ] pre-commit config exists`\n- `[ ] BUILD_TESTING block in CMakeLists.txt`\n- `[ ] ament_lint_auto in BUILD_TESTING block`\n- `[ ] launch tests for nodes`\n- `[ ] package README exists`\n- `[ ] .agents/README.md exists`\n\nOutput is a simple checklist showing what's present and what's missing.\n\n#### 4. Issue Template for Package Improvements\n\nA GitHub issue template (in project repos) for tracking quality improvements to a specific package. Pre-populated with the checklist items so agents can check them off as they're addressed across multiple PRs.\n\n### Integration with Existing Infrastructure\n\n- Builds on the existing documentation template (`.agent/templates/package_documentation.md`) and verification workflow (`.agent/knowledge/documentation_verification.md`)\n- Builds on the existing `.agents/README.md` project guide template (`.agent/templates/project_agents_guide.md`)\n- The audit script could be integrated with `worktree_enter.sh` to run automatically when entering a new package\n\n### Implementation Order\n\n1. Write the quality standards knowledge file\n2. Create the audit script\n3. Add the CLAUDE.md rule\n4. Create the issue template\n5. Pilot on 2-3 packages to validate the process\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}